stablishment of several awards  presented in the spring of each year  The Roberts Medal  Established in honor of John W  and Jane M  Roberts to recognize their lifelong interest in the American free enterprise system and their unswerving support for the Department of Economics and Business  The medal recognizes the top standing by an economics and business major in the graduating class  Class of 2008  Eric J  Hunter Class of 2009   Jacob N  Rochester Class of 2010   Daniel L  Welsh Class of 2011   Adam T  Kruithof Class of 2012   Michael A  Shafer Class of 2013   Simone R  Jiminez Class of 2014   Chih Yuan Chen   The Wheat Medal  Established in honor of James Clifton Wheat  Jr  Class of 1941  to acknowledge his lifelong interest in economics and business studies at VMI  and his leadership in the VMI Foundation s Economics Fund Drive  1969 1970  Up until the spring of 2008  the medal recognized excellence in economics studies by an Economics and Business major in the graduating class  Currently  the medal recognizes outstanding performance on the Major Field Test Business by an economics and business major in the graduating class  Class of 1971  Louis J  Cowardin  Jr  Class of 1972   Steven W  Palmer Class of 1973   Douglas K  Baumgardner Class of 1974   Albert J  Graham  III Class of 1975   Robert A  Lane Class of 1976   Kurt P  Luckenbill Class of 1977   Charles T  Floyd Class of 1978   Ivan A  Moore  Jr  Class of 1979   Nicholas C  Kepf Class of 1980   Robert B  Gore Class of 1981   Jeffrey M  Gill Class of 1982   Gordon R  Hammock Class of 1983   John C  Manning Class of 1984   Ralph A  Foertsch Class of 1985   Daniel W  Murphy Class of 1986   Joseph J  Thompson  III Class of 1987   Kevin P  Sincavage Class of 1988   Trent H  Beck Class of 1989   Thomas D  Shelton Class of 1990   John B  Cabell Class of 1991   Kyle A  Bryan Class of 1992   David F  Brugger Class of 1993   Troy D  Spencer Class of 1994   Nicolas B  Schweizer Class of 1995   Jeremy Ingram Class of 1996   John D  Adams Class of 1997   David O  Cooper Class of 1998   Michael P  Harris Class of 1999   Micheal J  Rust Class of 2000   Michael P  Goldman Class of 2001   Sean J  Collins Class of 2002   Peter Sok Class of 2003   Jordan E  Fox Class of 2004   Brandon M  Smith Class of 2005   William K  DeShazor Class of 2006   Bradley B  Bascope Class of 2006   Tadas Mandevicius Class of 2007   Richard Meredith Class of 2008   Garrett R  Smith Class of 2009  Daniel C  Allen Class of 2010   Daniel L  Welsh Class of 2011   Nathanael R  Salatin Class of 2012   Michael W  Bowman Class of 2013   William D  Alewine Class of 2014   William M  Breakell   The Philpott Medal  Established in honor of John Robert Philpott  Class of 1935  to acknowledge his efforts as National Chairman of the Economics Fund Drive  which resulted in the establishment of the Mary Moody Northen Chair in the Arts and Social Sciences  Until the spring of 2008  the medal recognized excellence in business studies by an Economics and Business major in the graduating class  Currently  the medal recognizes outstanding performance in research by an economics and business major in the graduating class  Class of 1987   Ronald A  Robinson  Jr  Class of 1988   Trent H  Beck Class of 1989   Thomas D  Shelton Class of 1990   Robert J  Uhorchuk  II Class of 1991   David K  Raucher Class fo 1992   Mark C  Thackston Class of 1993   C  Van Hardenbergh Class of 1994   Nicolas B  Schweizer Class of 1995   Jeremy Ingram Class of 1996   John D  Adams Class of 1997   David O  Cooper Class of 1998   Kenneth C  Dohanish           Michael T  Runyan Class of 1999   Dylan S  Williams Class of 2000   Michael P  Goldman Class of 2001   Nicholas R  Pohoreskey Class of 2002   Matthew S  Mitchell Class of 2003   Robert L  McLean Class of 2004   John Patrick Gregory Class of 2005   William K  DeShazor Class of 2006   Bradley B  Bascope Class of 2007   Richard Meredith Class of 2008   Rhys D  Williams Class of 2009   Andrew M  Krumm Class of 2010   n a Class of 2011   Nathanael R  Salatin Class of 2012   Boris Z  Duvnjak Class of 2013   Simone R  Jiminez Class of 2014   n a Academic Excellence 2012 Recipients 2011 Recipients 2010 Recipients 2009 Recipients 2008 Recipients 2007 Recipients VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu Virginia Military Institute   EC BU Awards  skip to content VMI VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI Menu About About Us Administrative Offices Institute Report News  Photos  Videos VMI Archives Museums VMI Museum System The VMI Museum New Market Battlefield Stonewall Jackson House For Visitors Directions   Map Employment Parents   Family Conferences Chessie Nature Trail Bookstore Resources MyVMI Directories Friendly URLs Post View Health and Safety Computing Academics Areas of Study Majors   Minors Arts   Humanities Engineering Information   Social Sciences Life Sciences Natural Sciences ROTC Enrichment Institute Honors Program International Programs Service Opportunities Summer Programs Institute Writing Program Research Support Cadet Counseling Career Services Disabilities Services Miller Academic Center Advising Math Resource Center The Writing Center Resources Registrar Financial Aid Canvas Login Dean s Office Career Services Bookstore Cadet Computing Admissions Corps Life Athletics Library   Archives Preston Library Library Home Find Books Departments Media Equipment Technical Services Visito